<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n56188b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56188b">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56188b"> 188(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> The Hat My / Father Wore</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Another song <font color="green">[<i>Where Did You Get that Hat?</i>]</font> which has become a mere catch phrase to us moderns! Written and sung by Joseph J. Sullivan in the late &apos;Eighties, it had an Irish flavour. There was an earlier song, <mark><i>The Hat My Father Wore</i></mark>, by Daniel McCarthy, which undoubtedly influenced <font color="green">[it]</font>. <small> Sigmund Spaeth, <a name="REAW3" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#REAW3"><cite title="source">Read 'Em and Weep</cite></a> (1935) 154</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
